en_162640_0	President Donald Trump has announced that the US is withdrawing from the 2015 Paris climate agreement.
en_162640_1	He said moves to negotiate a new "fair" deal that would not disadvantage US businesses and workers would begin.
en_162640_2	Trump said during last year's presidential election campaign that he would take the step to help his country's oil and coal industries.
en_162640_3	Opponents say withdrawing from the accord is an abdication of US leadership on a key global challenge.
en_162640_4	The Paris agreement commits the US and 187 other countries to keeping global temperatures rises "well below" 2C (3.6F) and "endeavour to limit" them even more, to 1.5C.
en_162640_5	Only Syria and Nicaragua did not sign up to the deal.
